<P><B>TopCoder Reduces Single Round Matches to Once Per Week and Removes Prize Money</B></P>

<P>
Starting on July 1, 2002, two important changes at TopCoder will take effect.  First, prize money will be removed from Single Round Matches, and secondly, the frequency of Single Round Matches will be reduced from twice per week to once per week.  Instead of focusing on sponsorships for Single Round Matches, TopCoder will shift its focus toward developing commercial software by utilizing the talent of the TopCoder members.  The Single Round Matches will be utilized as qualification opportunities for major prize paying tournaments and as an initial screening process for development work on TopCoder Software projects.  The reduction in frequency of the matches is a factor of the man power necessary to set up and administer the events.  TopCoder will look in the future to transitioning much of the administration of the matches to the member base, potentially resulting in an increase of Single Round Matches in the future.
</P>

<P><BR/></P>
<P>
About TopCoder, Inc.<BR/>
TopCoder, Inc. organizes and hosts online and onsite programming competitions for its members.  With a global membership database, TopCoder members extend across all professional and collegiate levels.  The best performing members are invited to compete in annual tournaments.  The attraction of competition and the associated rewards create a powerful community of programmers.  Access to this community is granted to corporate partners who both promote and profit from the relationship.  For more information and registration details visit www.topcoder.com.</P>


